Readme notes

To activate myenv : 
source myenv/Scripts/activate

To start the mvc : 
python app.py

To create datas for test:
I created a createPost.py file that creates json files for testing 
tests to create posts that can be deleted, updated or
be deleted, updated

To display the data :
curl -X GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/posts

To create a post :
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title": "Mon titre", "body": "Contenu post" "author": "Auteur"}' http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/v1/posts

To delete a post in the terminal:
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/v1/posts/ID

To confirm to delete :
curl -X DELETE "http://localhost:5000/api/v1/posts/ID?confirm=true"

To update :
curl -X PUT -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title": "Nouveau titre", "body": "Nouveau contenu", "author": "Nouvel auteur"}' http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/v1/posts/ID


HTTP response status codes indicate whether a specific HTTP 

Status Code: 200
Description: The request was successful, and the server has returned the requested data.
Usage in Code: Returned when a post is successfully deleted from the database. It indicates that the deletion process was successful, and the post was removed.

Status Code: 201
The request succeeded, and a new resource was created as a result. This is typically the response sent after POST requests, or some PUT requests.

Status Code: 400
The server cannot or will not process the request due to something that is perceived to be a client error (e.g., malformed request syntax, invalid request message framing, or deceptive request routing).

Status Code: 404 
Not Found
Description: The server could not find the requested resource.
Usage in Code: Returned when attempting to delete a post with an ID that does not exist in the database. It indicates that the post was not found and, therefore, cannot be deleted.

Status Code: 500
Description: The server encountered an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request.
Usage in Code: Returned if there is an error during the deletion process that is not expected or handled explicitly. This could include database errors or other unexpected exceptions.

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Status